('1101064', 'Indrias Putri Pratiwi', 'Program Customer Relationship Management Dalam Upaya Meningkatkan Loyalitas Tamu Hotel Sweet Karina ', 'Manajemen Pemasaran Pariwisata', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN ILMU PENGETAHUAN SOSIAL', 'Heny Hendrayati, S.IP., M.M.', 'Dewi Pancawati Novalita, M.M.', 'Pariwisata merupakan kegiatan yang di dalamnya di dukung oleh atraksi, akomodasi, dll. salah satu akomodasi yang disediakan adalah hotel. bandung merupakan kota tujuan wisata yang banyak diminati. seiring berjalannya waktu semakin banyak hotel di kota bandung. sweet karina hotel merupakan hotel bintang 3 di bandung. semakin banyak pesaing di daerah sekitar hotel sweet karina, maka akan berdampak buruk bagi hotel sweet karina. hal tersebut akan mengurangi jumlah tamu yang datang dan loyalitas tamu. oleh karena itu, hotel sweet karina menggunakan program customer relationship management dalam upaya meningkatkan loyalitas tamu hotel sweet karina bandung', '2016', 'indriasptr@gmail.com'),
('1101065', 'Meitha Herlina Rahman', 'IMPLEMENTING CRITICAL READING MODEL IN TEACHING READING HORTATORY TEXT (A Case Study Conducted in a ', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Gin Gin Gustine, M.Pd., Ph.D.', '', 'This paper aims to examine how critical reading model is implemented in teaching hortatory exposition text in English as foreign languge classroom. The subject of this study are the students of 11th grade of Linguistic Program in one senior high school in Bandung. The data obtained through classroom observation of teaching phase taking six meetings, individual interview toward randomly selected participants, distcributing questionnaire ad conducting reading model through five strategies which are previewing, identifying arguments and claims, weighing evidence, evaluating evidence and summarizing. Besides, it is also found that critical reading model is able to help students in their reading ability since the result of reading test showed that 18 out of 30 students having good score on reading test. Moreover, 83.3 5 of students think that they do not have any difficulties in learning using this ...', '2016', 'meitha.herlina@gmail.com'),
